This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with vision tasks and proposes a method to address data imbalance in such tasks. It is also likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as it proposes a novel method for improving predictive accuracy. The paper also involves the use of decision forests, which are commonly used in data science (cs.DS) and neural networks (cs.NE), which are commonly used in deep learning.
